data.title: Celsius Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ: CELH) shares surged after delivering upbeat quarterly results. Q4 adjusted EPS was 26 cents, surpassing estimates, with sales of $721.628 million (+117% YoY). CEO noted a 20% market share increase in the U.S. energy drink category. Retail sales for Celsius, Alani Nu, and Rockstar Energy all saw growth, with Alani Nu showing the highest increase at 76.9%. North America sales reached $699.5 million, while International sales hit $22.1 million.
data.description: Celsius Holdings, Inc. saw their shares rise after reporting strong quarterly performance. They exceeded expectations with adjusted earnings per share of 26 cents, beating the estimated 20 cents. Quarterly sales were $721.628 million, a 117% increase year over year, surpassing the expected $640.834 million. The company's CEO highlighted reaching a 20% dollar share of the U.S. energy drink category in Q4 2025. North America sales grew by 124% to $699.5 million, while international sales rose by 9% to $22.1 million. In retail performance, Celsius Holdings' portfolio retail sales increased by 24.4% in tracked U.S. channels, with the CELSIUS brand racking up a 12.8% increase, Alani Nu growing by 76.9%, and Rockstar Energy witnessing a decline of 10.3%.

data.title: Hormel Q1: EPS beats at 34 cents, sales miss at $3.03B. Operating income $244M, cash flow at $349M, retail volume down 6%.
data.description: Hormel Foods Corp's (NYSE: HRL) stock experienced a decline following the release of their first-quarter FY26 results. The company posted adjusted earnings per share of 34 cents, surpassing the analyst estimate of 32 cents. However, their sales figure of $3.03 billion fell short of the expected $3.07 billion. Operating income was reported at $244 million, with adjusted operating income at $247 million, resulting in operating and adjusted operating margins of 8% and 8.2% respectively. Cash flow from operations for the quarter amounted to $349 million. Inventories at the end of the quarter totaled $1.6 billion, while they had cash reserves of $868 million. In terms of segment performance, retail volume saw a 6% decrease and net sales dropped by 2%, influenced by the company's strategic withdrawal from specific non-core private label snack nut products and challenges in branded items.

data.title: IntelePeer partners with Your Social Smile to enhance dental patient engagement, workflow automation, and revenue growth.
data.description: In a recent announcement, IntelePeer has joined forces with Your Social Smile to enhance their Agentic AI solutions geared towards improving patient engagement, streamlining workflows, and boosting dental revenue growth. The collaboration, effective as of Feb. 26, 2026, is part of IntelePeer's strategy to expand their offerings in this area. This partnership signifies an important step for both companies as they leverage their expertise to provide innovative solutions in the dental industry.

data.title: CPKC completed filing 2025 Form 10-K; includes annual report and financial statements.
data.description: Calgary-based Canadian Pacific Kansas City announced on February 26, 2026, that it has successfully submitted its 2025 annual report on Form 10-K to the U.S. authorities. data.title: $1.1 million grant helps transform historic hotel in Brownsville, Texas into affordable housing apartments.
data.description: In Brownsville, Texas, the Housing Authority of the City (HACB) marked the grand opening of El Jardin as a renewed affordable residential community downtown. This transformation was made possible with a $1.1 million grant from the Federal Home Loan Bank of Dallas (FHLB Dallas) through Texas Regional Bank. El Jardin, an establishment initially constructed in 1927 as a hotel and later abandoned in the late 1980s, has been revitalized to provide housing options for the community.

data.description: A commercial moving company in the Washington DC region has recently acquired Hoffberger Moving Services and Re-form, becoming the only office mover in the area dedicated solely to commercial clients. This acquisition marks a significant expansion for the company, adding to its portfolio of clients and increasing its operational capacity. This move solidifies the company's position as a key player in the commercial moving industry in the region.

data.title: Table Trac declares quarterly dividend of $0.02/share, payable on March 27, 2026, with record date on March 13, 2026.

data.title: Eli Lilly's new oral weight loss drug outperforms Novo Nordisk's drug in a Phase 3 trial with 1,698 participants, eyeing US approval in Q2.
data.description: Shares of Eli Lilly and Co. (NYSE: LLY) experienced a decline on Thursday following the company's announcement of positive results for its oral GLP-1 medication, orforglipron. In the ACHIEVE-3 trial, the first head-to-head Phase 3 study comparing orforglipron with Novo Nordisk A/S' (NYSE: NVO) oral semaglutide in adults with type 2 diabetes inadequately managed with metformin, 1,698 participants were enrolled for the 52-week trial. The outcomes revealed that orforglipron surpassed oral semaglutide in primary and secondary endpoints, demonstrating notable enhancements in A1C levels and weight loss. In the most recent update, Eli Lilly disclosed that orforglipron 36 mg exhibited superior efficacy compared to oral semaglutide 14 mg in a Phase 3 trial, achieving a substantial 2.2% decrease in A1C levels.

data.title: Health care workers to rally at Doug Ford’s office over 10% hospital funding cut by 2027-28, causing staff shortages.
data.description: In Toronto, healthcare workers under the Canadian Union of Public Employees are set to stage a rally outside Premier Doug Ford’s office in Etobicoke. This comes as a response to funding reductions by the provincial government. As per the government’s fall economic statement, there is a proposed plan to decrease hospital funding by 10% in real terms over three years, reaching 2027-28. This decision has been motivated by the fact that the projected spending does not suffice to cover the annual cost inflation of six percent for hospitals, according to CUPE. The repercussions of these fiscal measures are likely to impact the healthcare sector significantly.

data.title: Bluevine introduces tools for small business invoicing & payments, including ACH positive pay. JERSEY CITY, N.J., Feb. 26, 2026.
data.description: Bluevine has introduced new features aimed at simplifying and securing the payment process for businesses. These include the ability to generate estimates, incorporate discounts into invoices, and offer ACH positive pay for Premier customers. The company, based in Jersey City, N.J., unveiled the updates on Feb. 26, 2026. Bluevine is recognized as the leading digital banking platform, catering to a large customer base. Businesses can now leverage these enhancements to streamline their financial transactions and ensure enhanced security measures.

data.title: Wildbrine introduces first fermented bean salad - Mediterranean and Kimchi-Style, hitting Whole Foods Markets on April 1.
data.description: Wildbrine, known for their sauerkraut and kimchi products, is launching a groundbreaking line of Mediterranean and Kimchi-Style Fermented Chickpea Salads. This marks the first time fermented bean salads will be available in packaged form. The debut is set for April 1st at Whole Foods Markets. The announcement was made in Madison, Wisconsin on February 26, 2026. This innovation is expected to revolutionize the fermented foods market, with wide-reaching implications for health-conscious consumers.

data.title: Arna Pharma Inc. & Slate Run Pharmaceuticals to form joint venture for U.S. specialty pharmaceutical market.
data.description: In Austin, Texas on February 26, 2026, it was reported that Arna Pharma Inc. and Slate Run Pharmaceuticals have entered into a Memorandum of Understanding to establish a larger U.S.-based specialty pharmaceutical partnership. This venture will prioritize branded products, 505(b)(2) medications, and specialized generics. The agreement marks a significant collaboration in the pharmaceutical industry, signaling a strategic move towards expanding product offerings and market presence.
